# 📊 SQL Project Report – E-Commerce Sales Data Analysis

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates end-to-end SQL analysis on an E-Commerce Sales dataset using PostgreSQL. The objective is to transform raw transactional data into meaningful business insights through SQL queries, aggregate functions, conditional statements, Common Table Expressions (CTEs), Window Functions, Views, and analytical reporting.

The project covers sales performance, customer behavior, revenue trends, product analysis, shipping performance, payment methods, customer satisfaction, and return analysis. It simulates real-world business scenarios and showcases practical SQL skills required for Data Analyst roles.

## Objectives

* Analyze overall business performance.
* Measure revenue and sales trends over time.
* Understand customer purchasing behavior.
* Evaluate product category performance.
* Analyze country-wise and platform-wise sales.
* Measure customer satisfaction and return rates.
* Apply advanced SQL techniques for business reporting.

